main event: An oval-shaped object with two red lights in front and 10-12 green lights in the rear was observed flying over Laurinburg-Maxton AFB, North Carolina.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 100-200 feet wide.,The sighting lasted for approximately 10-15 minutes.,The object approached from the east at an altitude of 15,000 feet.,It was tracked by radar, despite no visual confirmation by the observer on radar.,Witnesses reported hearing a low humming sound during the observation.
sighted object: a large oval-shaped object with two red lights and multiple green lights
